# Hooks

Hooks are great for cleaning up your code.
They let you move useState, useEffect and other logic out of your components into separate files.

## Rules
- Must start with `use` (e.g. `useUserName`, `useSettings`)
- Always import React features at the top of the file
- Always return what the component needs (state + functions)

## Hooks in this project

### useUserName
Handles userName state, loading from localStorage, and saving to localStorage.
Returns: `userName`, `saveUserName`, `mounted`